data.text:
President of the Republic of Finland Alexander Stubb had a telephone conversation with Prime Minister of Denmark Mette Frederiksen on Monday 18 March 2024.

In addition to bilateral relations, President Stubb and Prime Minister Frederiksen discussed Nordic cooperation, preparations for the NATO summit in July and Russia’s war of aggression in Ukraine. President Stubb thanked Prime Minister Frederiksen for Denmark’s strong contribution to Ukraine.
